    CalypsoPoDataOutOfBoundsException
    The exception CalypsoPoDataOutOfBoundsException indicates that the data provided by the user induces a capacity overflow in the PO.
    This can occur, for example, for commands that update a counter or the "Stored Value".

    CalypsoPoIllegalParameterException

    CalypsoPoPinException

    CalypsoPoSecurityContextException

    CalypsoPoSecurityDataException
    The exception CalypsoPoSecurityDataException indicates that the security input data provided is not valid.
    This can occur, for example, during the closing of a secure session if the SAM's signature is incorrect.
    CalypsoPoSessionBufferOverflowException
    The exception CalypsoPoSessionBufferOverflowException indicates during a secure session that the PO session buffer will overflow.
    CalypsoPoTerminatedException
    The exception CalypsoPoTerminatedException indicates that the number of transactions authorized by the PO has reached its limit.
    This may occur, for example, when requesting an open secure session.
    CalypsoPoUnknownStatusException
    The exception CalypsoPoUnknownException indicates that the status code is not referenced.
